# ============================================================================ #
#  Grobase managed-cloud — THE SINGLE FLIP POINT for the B1–B7 feature flags    #
#  (Track-B B7.1 · plan: apps/baas/.claude/plans/managed-cloud-enterprise.md)   #
# ============================================================================ #
#
# This file is the ONE authoritative manifest of every managed-cloud behaviour
# flag. It is OPT-IN: the default stack NEVER reads it. The default
# docker-compose.yml + .env are byte-parity with the OSS self-host edition —
# every flag below already defaults OFF *inside the services themselves* (Go
# main.go's envBool gates, the Rust config.rs gates), so an absent or all-OFF
# manifest changes nothing.
#
# An operator turns a feature ON for a hosted environment by:
#   1. cp config/cloud/flags.env.example config/cloud/flags.<env>.env
#   2. flip the ladder rung(s) for that env (see config/cloud/README.md)
#   3. source it into the stack's .env, e.g.
#        cat config/cloud/flags.staging.env >> .env   (or via your secrets tool)
#   4. recreate the control plane: make up EDITION=prod
#
# Inspect (no behaviour, just prints this file):  make cloud-flags-print
#
# RULES (kernel #5 — least change, reversible first):
#   • Every flag here is OFF by default. OFF = byte-parity with OSS.
#   • Promote one rung at a time (staging → canary → prod), never skip.
#   • Metering must be ON before quota/billing can do anything (they AND with
#     METERING_ENABLED in code — see metering/billing.go, metering/quotaguard.go).
#   • Enforcement (402s, spend caps, abuse suspends) is the LAST rung — shadow
#     and warn first (B7.2). A surprise 402 is an incident.
#
# Single source of truth for the FLAG NAMES: the service code that reads them
# (grep -rn '<FLAG>' go/control-plane). Do not invent flags here that no
# service consumes — that is a parity lie. Every flag below has a live consumer
# (B7.8 spend caps → internal/spendcap, B7.9 abuse guard → internal/abuseguard
# both landed + gate-proven, m89/m90); flipping one ON enables real behaviour.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
#  B1 · METERING — per-tenant usage counters (requests/rows/storage/realtime/fn)
#  Master switch: every downstream cloud feature ANDs with METERING_ENABLED.
#  (metering/consumer.go, metering/billing.go, metering/quotaguard.go)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
METERING_ENABLED=0
# control-plane consumer that drains the usage stream into tenant_usage
METERING_INGEST=0
# data-plane emits per-request usage events (Rust config.rs) — the producer side
DATA_PLANE_METERING=0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
#  B2 · QUOTA — HTTP 402 when a tenant exceeds its tier quota
#  STAGED rollout (B7.2): shadow → warn → enforce. NEVER jump straight to
#  enforce on a populated tenant. QUOTA_STAGE is the staged dial; the legacy
#  boolean QUOTA_ENFORCEMENT remains the hard on/off the code reads today
#  (quotaguard.go). Keep them congruent: stage=enforce ⇔ QUOTA_ENFORCEMENT=1.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# off | shadow | warn | enforce  — see config/cloud/README.md "promotion ladder".
# OFF here to honour the "every flag OFF by default = byte-parity" invariant
# above; an operator promotes shadow→warn→enforce per-env (flags.env.cloud).
QUOTA_STAGE=off
QUOTA_ENFORCEMENT=0
# how often the guard re-evaluates usage vs the tier limit (ms)
QUOTA_ENFORCEMENT_INTERVAL_MS=15000
# which metered counter the guard gates on
QUOTA_ENFORCEMENT_METRIC=query.count

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
#  B3 · BILLING — Stripe meter-event reporter consuming B1 usage
#  (metering/billing.go — ANDs with METERING_ENABLED; refuses to start if ON but
#  STRIPE_API_KEY / BILLING_METER_* are unset, so OFF is the safe default.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
BILLING_ENABLED=0
BILLING_REPORT_INTERVAL_MS=60000
# Stripe credential + the meter-id map (set per-env via your SECRETS tool, NOT
# committed). Empty here on purpose — these are the human/$$ atoms (plan §atoms).
STRIPE_API_KEY=
BILLING_METER_QUERY_COUNT=
BILLING_METER_QUERY_ROWS=
BILLING_METER_WRITE_ROWS=
BILLING_METER_STORAGE_BYTES=
BILLING_METER_REALTIME_MINUTES=
BILLING_METER_FUNCTION_INVOCATIONS=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
#  B4 · TENANT SELF-SERVICE — /v1/tenants/me* (read me/usage/keys, plan change)
#  (tenant-control main.go — MountSelfServe gated on TENANT_SELFSERVE_ENABLED.
#  NOTE: the LIVE docker-compose.yml already defaults this to 1 for tenant-
#  control; this manifest documents the cloud-canonical value. Self-serve routes
#  resolve the caller's OWN tenant — no cross-tenant access by construction.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
TENANT_SELFSERVE_ENABLED=0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
#  B5 · PER-TENANT OBSERVABILITY — tenant_id as a log FIELD (not a Prom label),
#  bounded counter + Grafana view. (shared/logger.go reads TENANT_OBS_ENABLED;
#  data plane reads DATA_PLANE_TENANT_OBS.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
TENANT_OBS_ENABLED=0
DATA_PLANE_TENANT_OBS=0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
#  B6 · PER-TENANT BACKUP/RESTORE — logical scoped backup/restore
#  (backup/handler.go — Mount + MountSelfServe gated on TENANT_BACKUP_ENABLED.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
TENANT_BACKUP_ENABLED=0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
#  B7.8 · SPEND CAPS — BUILT (internal/spendcap, wired in cmd/orchestrator;
#  gate m89-spend-caps.sh). Per-org budget + 80% alert + a $-cap that STOPS
#  billable service. GO-LIVE gates B7.7 signup on this (plan §GO-LIVE GATING).
#  ON needs SPEND_RATE_* set; OFF (default) = byte-parity.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
SPEND_CAPS_ENABLED=0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
#  B7.9 · ABUSE / FRAUD GUARD + free-tier KYC-lite — BUILT (internal/abuseguard,
#  mounted in cmd/tenant-control as /v1/abuse/*; gate m90-abuse-guard.sh).
#  email/phone verify, project-creation velocity, pay-method gating + suspend.
#  Also a hard GO-LIVE gate for public signup. OFF (default) = byte-parity.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
ABUSE_GUARD_ENABLED=0
